726137f-a.text:
Beach 19th Street, at the N.E. corner of Plainview Ave., showing the L. H. Donahue mansion from 1873 to 1891. It is now known as the
Chelsea Hotel.
January 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726138f-a.text:
Beach 19th Street, west side, just north of Plainview Ave., showing the Far Rockaway Hotel of which M. Killoran was the proprietor in 1923.
It was known as the National Hotel from 1873 to 1891.
January 1923.
Eucene L. Armbruster Collection.
